race.comment: GOD'S GRIN (8) is knocking on the door of a maiden victory, finishing 0.4L off the winner as the favourite last time out. Barrier 13 is a query, but Pike remains in the saddle and she'll be fitter for the fresh run. Can build on the first-up performance and get the job done now. SPEAK OF THE DEVIL (1) comes through the same race as GOD'S GRIN, though he was a further 2 lengths behind that runner at Bunbury last time out. That effort still produced a solid rating and that looks like the key form reference for this. Appears the main danger off what we saw fresh. ROCK THE MIC (10) hit the line nicely in his latest trial and gets the blinkers on for his debut. Gaerth will have options from the draw and this trip first-up looks a good move. Can make his presence felt on debut. MAURICE'S PRINCESS (11) was good in her only run last campaign and is worth keeping safe despite a poor trial recently. DOBLE OH NADA (3) can bounce back following a disappointing performance last time out.
